// Balloons are intervals [x_start, x_end] on a number line.
// An arrow shot at position x bursts all balloons where x_start <= x <= x_end.
// Find the minimum number of arrows to burst all balloons.
// Input: n, then n pairs (x_start, x_end)
// Example: n=4, intervals={(10,16),(2,8),(1,6),(7,12)} => output: 2
// Example: n=2, intervals={(1,2),(3,4)} => output: 2

