// You have n children. Child i wants exactly a[i] candies.
// You have m distinct candy packs, each with b[j] candies.
// Assign each child at most one pack. A child is satisfied if b[j] >= a[i].
// Maximize the number of satisfied children.
// Input: n m, then array a (wishes), then array b (pack sizes)
// Example: n=3 m=3, a={3,1,2}, b={2,3,1} => output: 2
// Constraints: 1<=n,m<=2e5, 1<=a[i],b[j]<=1e9

